videoDetails.title: Mueller shows evidence of "obstruction of justice'': Jerrold Nadler
videoDetails.shortDescription: US House of Representatives Judiciary Committee Chairman Jerrold Nadler said on Thursday that the special counsel Robert Mueller's Russia investigation report outlines “disturbing evidence” that president Trump engaged in obstruction of justice. Nadler also accused attorney general William Barr of undermining his own department in order to protect Trump. He said it was “disingenuous and misleading” of Barr to say Trump is “clear of wrongdoing”. Barr is scheduled to testify before the committee on May 2. Nadler has requested Mueller testify before the committee because “we can’t believe what Barr tells us.” Nadler also said the report shows Mueller chose not to pursue charges, partly because of a Justice Department policy that a sitting president cannot be indicted.
videoDetails.author: Guardian News
